How to Run a script to convert the floating values into the decimal format
-------------------------------------------------------------------------


    ---> Make pdp8fp executable with the following command
            chmod +x pdp8fp

    ---> pdp8fp generates hex values by default

    ---> Use -h or -o for hex or octal generation. If you don't use any flags it will take hex values automatically

            Example:
                    ./pdp8fp 
                        It will run the input file of floating point values in hex and will put the output in fp_out file

                    ./pdp8fp -h
                        It will run the input file of floating point values in hex and will put the output in fp_out file
                     
                     ./pdp8fp -o
                         It will run the input file of floating point values in octal and puts the output in fp_out file

    ---> Give any value while running the script to generate the pdp8 floating point format.

            Example:
                    ./pdp8fp 83.4234
                        It will display the pdp8 floating point value format in hex by default.

                    ./pdp8fp -h 83.4234
                        It will display the pdp8 floating point value format in hex.
                    
                    ./pdp8fp -o 83.4234
                    It will display the pdp8 floating point value format in octal
                    
*****************************************************************************************************************************************
